summary:
After my Masters in Mass Communication, I have gained over 10 years experience at the crossroads of marketing, communication, branding, event and project management, PR, production of campaigns & publications, and creative design. I have enjoyed working for government, for-profit, non-profit, and agencies like DDB. 

Whether in large organizations, small organizations, or lately within my own freelance agency called MASE Pte Ltd, I have been able to work as a self-starter but always enjoyed working with people. Others have described me as enthusiastic, creative, result driven, imaginative and resourceful.

My most enjoyable achievements have been those that allowed me to be creative and focus on design. Throughout the years, my passion for design has become stronger and stronger. In 2012, I started a course in Jewelry Design & Metalsmithing. I love creating designs in my home studio and produce my own simple, stylish silver jewelry. In 2016 I launched MASE Handmade Jewelry, a jewelry brand inspired by lines & shapes in everyday life. To feel that little bit more wonderful on an ordinary day.

Born and raised in the Netherlands, I love to travel around the world, especially in Asia. I have been living in Singapore since 2005 and enjoy exploring its culture and creative styles, trends, hidden boutiques, and backstreet gems. I am holding a Singapore PR.
